Maciej Pilitowski (born 27 October 1990) is a Polish handball player for Energa MKS Kalisz and the Polish national team.


== Career ==


=== National team ===
Pilitowski made his debut for the national team on January 4, 2013, in a friendly match against Hungary (27:29). He was also chosen to participate at the 2014 European Championship in Denmark, but failed to make it to the final squad.


